		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">In continuation of our successful programme on magnetic structures and phase transitions using x-ray MAGNETIC scattering, we wish to study mixed crystals of (antiferromagnetic) Uas and (ferromagnetic) Use using the X22C diffractometer at the NSLS, BNL, USA.  We have been allocated peer-reviewed beamtime in March 1998, with a further at ESRF, Grenoble. The CRG beamline is in the final stages of preparation for the user programme.Measurements are to be made on two aspects, building on our previous Uas-Use experiments at X22C.  First, the concentration and x-ray energy dependences  of a new magnetic modulation discovered for a 20% Se sample are to be investigated for lower doping.  Second, very anisotropic critical scattering lineshapes will be studied for small Se doping  (<10%).  On completion of these measurements, similar work on the Usb-Ute system is planned.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
